# Universal Language (UL) Modding & Extensibility Guidelines

## Purpose
Defines best practices and extension points for modders to add new UL puzzles, scripts, and resources.

## Supported Extensions
- New puzzles/resources via JSON files in `assets/lang/ul/` or `mods/`
- Custom validation scripts (must be sandboxed)
- Metadata tags for mod tracking
- UI hooks for custom feedback or accessibility

## Requirements
- All resources must conform to `ul_resource_schema_2025-06-06.artifact`
- Scripts must be safe and pass static analysis
- Mods should register via documented API (see src/mods/)

## Best Practices
- Use unique IDs and namespaces
- Document all new events or hooks
- Provide test cases for new puzzles/scripts

## References
- See `ul_system_technical_spec_2025-06-06.artifact` and `ul_event_spec_2025-06-06.artifact`.
